column5: Went out Walleye fishing at Sunset Bay. We got 11 Walleye's....dipsey divers and leadcore and worm harness were the ticket...
Ok.  Enough,s enough.  Mods,please limit Doug to one post a month with these crazy pickerel Erie reports. LOL  Your having a great season there Doug. Real nice.
You've certainly got those yellow fish dialed in Doug, great day for you as usual.

I think you will agree Doug, best Picker, er I mean Walleye fishing here in years. Now the big Mama smallies are starting their feed on the shoals as these Pics move your way to the south side, pal got into a few Bass this morning  dropshoting before the Hurricaine set in, a 5 and a 6 pounder.
Looks like a beautiful day on the water, nice fish
